body:
C’mon, wake up | Peter Parker

Summary: (y/n) just wanted to help… boy, did that go wrong…

Pairing: fem!reader x peter parker

Words: 1,329

Warnings: blood, death, angst, swearing

(a/n: This is a 100% inspired by the scene where Gwen Stacy dies in The Amazing Spider-Man 2, I’m all about that type of angst tbh. Sorry for the poor writing tho, it’s my first time writing a fanfic in english and I’m pretty self-conscious of it too, but please, send me some feedback, I do want to improve my english writing skills (but if you’re just gonna be plain rude, please save yourself some time, only constructive criticism please). Thanks for reading, I hope you like it!)

Tag-list and Mutuals: (if you don’t want to be tagged, do please ask me or message me) @hollandandi @petalparker @fratboievans @thwippeter @thothollandd @fallingforparker @scotlang @hollandsosterfield @hollandroos @nxverlandtom @moonkissedtom @spiderlingss @spiderboytotherescue @spidereyhes @starksparker @starksmile @mcufam

The wind blew colder that night, announcing autumn’s arrival. The air was wrapping all around her, making the jacket she had on totally useless. Shivers ran through her body and she could feel how her cheeks and nose had gotten red. Autumn was her favorite season of all, and (Y/N) could’ve appreciated it at least a little bit more, if it wasn’t for the fight that was happening right in front of her. It was a battle between Peter and Harry. Spider-Man against Green Goblin.

They were in the top of an abandoned building just outside the city, the perfect place so she couldn’t get help. (Y/N) blamed herself because if it wasn’t for her stupidity, she wouldn’t have gotten herself kidnapped, and there would be no fight right now. But of course, she ran straight to the trap Harry planted for her.

Peter looked exhausted, (Y/N) could tell, by the way he slowed down a bit. He punched Harry in the face and he, quick on his feet, returned the punch, making Peter fall back a little. (Y/N) recognized Harry’s strength equals Peter’s, making a tie between them, but the way Peter looked and moved; one could easily tell he was getting tired.

Peter made a false move and Harry got him under his grip, strangling him. He looked terrifying, with crazy eyes and a horrid grin across Harry’s face that showed how much he was enjoying   having his neck in between his hands while constricting it. (Y/N) was terrified by the sight and saw that Peter wasn’t going to get out of it soon enough, she grown anxious and she instantly knew she had to do something as quick as possible. Her nerves got worse when she saw Peter started to black out.

She grabbed the first thing she saw on the ground that was heavy enough and, with all her strength, threw it at Harry, successfully hitting him in the head and letting go of Peter, who fell to the ground unconscious.

“Leave him alone!” her voice was crisp.

Harry, filled with even more anger, wiped out the blood that dripped down to his forehead, and chuckled. With his glider, he rapidly flew to where (Y/N) was and, before she had a chance to run away, he grabbed her by the neck and lifted her up. Meanwhile, Peter slowly started to regain consciousness.

“You’ve always been a pain in the ass, you knew that?” (Y/N) looked at him, twitching in his hands, trying oh-so desperately to catch some air. Harry smiled at the spectacle. “Even in high school, trying so hard to be head of the class.” he scoffed cynically.

(Y/N), in desperation, reaches out to one of the pumpkin grenades from Harry’s belt and turned one on. She took in a sharp breath. “And you’ve always been a fucking idiot.” she growled.

Harry finally unconstrained her, dropping her at the very edge of the tall building, where she stayed still, trying to catch her breath, and holding her bruised neck. Harry managed to take the grenade off his suit and throw it away from him, but it still blew up very close, knocking him out of the glider, where he hit his head and lost awareness.

Unfortunately, the grenade was also close to (Y/N) and the magnitude of the explosion pushed her away and, consequently, fell off the building. At the exact moment, Peter regained conscious and, as he saw how she propelled off the building, got up in an instant, threw himself off of the roof, and fired his web shooter at her, in hopes of catching her.

Everything went in slow motion.

(Y/N) glared at Peter, still falling. She saw how the web kept coming at her, but it wasn’t fast enough. She felt how the cold air, that she just noticed a few moments ago, hit her body brutally as she descended.

Suddenly, the face of her mom passed through her mind, at how she fought with her before she left the house earlier that evening, and it was a stupid fight about something she can no longer remember. She regretted that. And so, the first tear came out of her eyes.

Her sister, her tiny little sister, who she loved immensely. She remembered that one time where she got her for a present in her birthday a doll she just couldn’t stop talking about. She got so happy with the sight of her baby sister playing and humming with that doll every day. The giggles made everyday a happy day. More tears came along.

And Peter.

The person she loved the most.

The person she would do anything for.

She remembered the first time she met him. They were still at high school and one day, she was on her way to return some books, when all of the sudden, she stumbled on Peter. They were both distracted, her still reading one of the books and him writing something on a notebook, which he revealed later on in their relationship was a new web formula.

The first time they kissed was one of her favorite days of her life. Peter was really nervous and couldn’t stop blushing, but (Y/N) was calm, wanting it to happen, because she was already falling for him. When they finally did it, it was the most amazing kiss of all, she never felt something like that in her life and she loved it. After that, Peter stopped being nervous around her, and even though she liked that about him, she accepted with open arms that he finally got to be comfortable around her.

She really loved him.

She loved the way his curly hair felt so soft in between her fingers, she loved the color of his eyes and how much they would shine whenever the sunlight hit them, creating the most amazing golden eyes. She loved his smile and the way he would only smile at her, and only her. She loved his jaw, his ears, and his nose. Everything about him she loved. Everything.

She still gazed at Peter and the web, which still was making its way at her.

But she knew, she just knew, it wasn’t going to catch her on time. Peter wasn’t going to catch her.

She wasn’t going to make it.

So, she gave up and closed her eyes, warm tears still coming out of them. She wasn’t sure, but she might have heard Peter screaming at her. All she could really hear was her heart pounding hard in her chest and the rush of the air in her ears.

She opened her eyes.

“I’m sorry.” she whispers.

And finally, everything went dark.

Peter stopped immediately at a window sill after hearing the horrendous thud. His breath caught in his lungs, while paralyzed, seeing (Y/N)’s motionless body on the ground.

“No, no, no…” he kept repeating himself, barely as a whisper.

He jumped and landed softly next to (Y/N), picking her up in his arms instantly as gentle as possible. Everything was silent, except for the sound of Peter’s sob and his intake of sharp breaths. His eyes were red and burning, tears overflowing them, almost making it impossible for him to see.

“(Y/N), honey…” he trembled, while he tried to swallow the big rock that was stuck in his throat, “C’mon baby, wake up.” he commanded, taking harsh breaths.

Blood dripped from her head and came out of her nose and mouth. Peter, with all his strength being pulled out of him, sat down, her still in his arms. He stroked her hair, letting the blood soak his hands. It was still warm and that hurt him even more.

“No!” he bawled, tears running wild across his cheeks. “(Y/N), come back, please!” he pleaded.

He hugged her as tight as he could, putting his head in her chest, trying to hear a single heart beat, but only silence met him.

“I’m sorry,” he wept, crushed. “I’m so sorry.”

The wind blew colder that night, announcing autumn’s arrival. The air was wrapping all around her, making the jacket she had on totally useless. Shivers ran through her body and she could feel how her cheeks and nose had gotten red. Autumn was her favorite season of all, and (Y/N) could’ve appreciated it at least a little bit more, if it wasn’t for the fight that was happening right in front of her. It was a battle between Peter and Harry. Spider-Man against Green Goblin.

They were in the top of an abandoned building just outside the city, the perfect place so she couldn’t get help. (Y/N) blamed herself because if it wasn’t for her stupidity, she wouldn’t have gotten herself kidnapped, and there would be no fight right now. But of course, she ran straight to the trap Harry planted for her.

Peter looked exhausted, (Y/N) could tell, by the way he slowed down a bit. He punched Harry in the face and he, quick on his feet, returned the punch, making Peter fall back a little. (Y/N) recognized Harry’s strength equals Peter’s, making a tie between them, but the way Peter looked and moved; one could easily tell he was getting tired.

Peter made a false move and Harry got him under his grip, strangling him. He looked terrifying, with crazy eyes and a horrid grin across Harry’s face that showed how much he was enjoying   having his neck in between his hands while constricting it. (Y/N) was terrified by the sight and saw that Peter wasn’t going to get out of it soon enough, she grown anxious and she instantly knew she had to do something as quick as possible. Her nerves got worse when she saw Peter started to black out.

She grabbed the first thing she saw on the ground that was heavy enough and, with all her strength, threw it at Harry, successfully hitting him in the head and letting go of Peter, who fell to the ground unconscious.

“Leave him alone!” her voice was crisp.

Harry, filled with even more anger, wiped out the blood that dripped down to his forehead, and chuckled. With his glider, he rapidly flew to where (Y/N) was and, before she had a chance to run away, he grabbed her by the neck and lifted her up. Meanwhile, Peter slowly started to regain consciousness.

“You’ve always been a pain in the ass, you knew that?” (Y/N) looked at him, twitching in his hands, trying oh-so desperately to catch some air. Harry smiled at the spectacle. “Even in high school, trying so hard to be head of the class.” he scoffed cynically.

(Y/N), in desperation, reaches out to one of the pumpkin grenades from Harry’s belt and turned one on. She took in a sharp breath. “And you’ve always been a fucking idiot.” she growled.

Harry finally unconstrained her, dropping her at the very edge of the tall building, where she stayed still, trying to catch her breath, and holding her bruised neck. Harry managed to take the grenade off his suit and throw it away from him, but it still blew up very close, knocking him out of the glider, where he hit his head and lost awareness.

Unfortunately, the grenade was also close to (Y/N) and the magnitude of the explosion pushed her away and, consequently, fell off the building. At the exact moment, Peter regained conscious and, as he saw how she propelled off the building, got up in an instant, threw himself off of the roof, and fired his web shooter at her, in hopes of catching her.

Everything went in slow motion.

(Y/N) glared at Peter, still falling. She saw how the web kept coming at her, but it wasn’t fast enough. She felt how the cold air, that she just noticed a few moments ago, hit her body brutally as she descended.

Suddenly, the face of her mom passed through her mind, at how she fought with her before she left the house earlier that evening, and it was a stupid fight about something she can no longer remember. She regretted that. And so, the first tear came out of her eyes.

Her sister, her tiny little sister, who she loved immensely. She remembered that one time where she got her for a present in her birthday a doll she just couldn’t stop talking about. She got so happy with the sight of her baby sister playing and humming with that doll every day. The giggles made everyday a happy day. More tears came along.

And Peter.

The person she loved the most.

The person she would do anything for.

She remembered the first time she met him. They were still at high school and one day, she was on her way to return some books, when all of the sudden, she stumbled on Peter. They were both distracted, her still reading one of the books and him writing something on a notebook, which he revealed later on in their relationship was a new web formula.

The first time they kissed was one of her favorite days of her life. Peter was really nervous and couldn’t stop blushing, but (Y/N) was calm, wanting it to happen, because she was already falling for him. When they finally did it, it was the most amazing kiss of all, she never felt something like that in her life and she loved it. After that, Peter stopped being nervous around her, and even though she liked that about him, she accepted with open arms that he finally got to be comfortable around her.

She really loved him.

She loved the way his curly hair felt so soft in between her fingers, she loved the color of his eyes and how much they would shine whenever the sunlight hit them, creating the most amazing golden eyes. She loved his smile and the way he would only smile at her, and only her. She loved his jaw, his ears, and his nose. Everything about him she loved. Everything.

She still gazed at Peter and the web, which still was making its way at her.

But she knew, she just knew, it wasn’t going to catch her on time. Peter wasn’t going to catch her.

She wasn’t going to make it.

So, she gave up and closed her eyes, warm tears still coming out of them. She wasn’t sure, but she might have heard Peter screaming at her. All she could really hear was her heart pounding hard in her chest and the rush of the air in her ears.

She opened her eyes.

“I’m sorry.” she whispers.

And finally, everything went dark.

Peter stopped immediately at a window sill after hearing the horrendous thud. His breath caught in his lungs, while paralyzed, seeing (Y/N)’s motionless body on the ground.

“No, no, no…” he kept repeating himself, barely as a whisper.
